    "keyword_id": "28",
    "keyword_tx": "Hotel",
    "letter_tx": "h",
    "lookup_tx": "hotel",
    "content_tx": "<p>A hotel is an establishment that provides lodging and sometimes meals, entertainment and various personal services for the public. RCA breaks hotels into the following subtypes:</p><p><b>Limited-Service:</b> A hotel is likely to be classified as limited service if it satisfies these conditions:</p><ul><li>Does not have room service</li><li>Does not have an on-site restaurant</li><li>Does not have a concierge</li> </ul> <p><b>Full-Service:</b> A hotel is likely to be classified as full service if it satisfies these conditions:</p><ul><li>Has room service</li><li>Has onsite restaurant</li> </ul> <p><b>Boutique:</b> A hotel is likely to be classified as Boutique if the following are true:</p><ul><li>Located in an urban or resort location</li><li>Has full-service amenities</li><li>Is not part of a national chain such as a Hilton</li><li>Is smaller scale (fewer than ~200 rooms)</li> </ul> <p><b>Casino:</b> A hotel is likely to be classified as Casino if the following are true:</p><ul><li>Most casinos are full-service; however, a few limited-service casinos exist.</li><li>A hotel should have a casino subtype if it has a gaming component (e.g., video poker, slot machines, table games, sports betting).</li><li>The Casino feature supersedes all other features. Thus if it is a casino and a resort, then the casino subtype is used because it has a greater impact on the value of the property.</li> </ul> <p><b>Extended Stay:</b> Extended Stay properties are always limited service.</p><ul><li>A hotel is likely to be classified as extended stay if it satisfies these conditions:</li><li>Has fully equipped kitchens in the guest rooms</li><li>Larger rooms suitable for long stays</li><li>Is one of the franchises on the extended stay list</li> </ul> <p><b>Resort:</b> A hotel is likely to be classified as Resort if the following are true:</p><ul><li>The property is full service</li><li>The property has a large amount of land</li><li>The property is situated in a typical \"resort\" location such as Hawaii, Orlando, or on a beach.</li><li>The property has an attached golf course, water park, or amusement facility.</li> </ul> <p><b>Suite:</b> Offers more space and furniture than a basic hotel room</p><p>Hotels of any kind must include at least 10 units for inclusion in the RCA database.</p>",
    "create_dt": "03/23/2012",
    "status_tx": "1"
